## NOTE: This analysis looks at men over 50.

Notes on Data Sources

Methane and sulfur dioxide readings collected in real-time by Fenceline.org

Heart rate collected with Fitbit health monitors

Blood Oxygen levels recorded with a pulse oximeter1

Correlations

Plots2

t-tests for Statistical Significance3

These tests compare the difference between the population mean health outcome (e.g.heart rate) and the mean health outcome when the environmental input (e.g.methane) is above its median value.

  2. For help on interpreting a correlation plot, visit this page

  3. Welch two-sample t-test
